snippet: As the biggest banks prepared to release quarterly earnings, the Dow and the Nasdaq were up and the S.& P. 500 stayed close to the five-year high it set on Thursday.
abstract: Stocks gain for second straight week as companies begin releasing earnings reports, keeping Standard & Poor's 500-stock index within fraction of its highest levels in five years.
lead_paragraph: As the biggest banks prepared to release quarterly earnings, the Dow and the Nasdaq were up and the S.& P. 500 stayed close to the five-year high it set on Thursday.

headline.main: Slim Gains in Markets Ahead of Earnings Reports
